      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TWO GIRLS (1) was strongly fancied latest and proved too good with a 1.5 lengths win at this track in a handy 19.36. Draws the cherry and goes well over this trip. In sparkling form with a string of wins and can measure up again. HIGHGATE PETE (7) turned in a solid run last start over 600m at Launceston finishing 4th and beaten only 2 lengths (35.10). Solid record here at the distance winning five races. One of the better chances. SILENT PRAYER (4) was responsible for a modest effort most recently when fifth at Launceston over 278m behind Sherwood Boys (16.55) in a Grade 5. Placed at her previous run. Key player if finds best. WHISKY BARREL (2) can return to form after missing the top-three at this circuit last time out.",
